    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-14T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-14T04:00:00-05:00" n="533"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d533">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4A6/394: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-14T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 14, 1931—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 14—7:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Department’s 22, July 13, 5 p.m. Will discuss convention with Wilson in Berne
                    today. Text was finally approved yesterday and signed by the following 28
                    countries: Austria, Belgium, Bolivia, Canada, Chile, Costa Rica, Cuba,
                    Czechoslovakia, Denmark, Ethiopia, France, Germany, Great Britain, Guatemala,
                    Hejaz, India, Italy, Japan, Mexico, The Netherlands, Panama, Paraguay, Portugal,
                    San Marino, Siam, Switzerland, Uruguay, Venezuela.</p>
                <p>Several other countries including Egypt and the Argentine anticipate signing
                    today.</p>
                <p>Am telegraphing full text of the convention in clear with the exception of
                    chemical formulae. Summary of the final act and protocol of signature being
                        telegraphed.<note n="9" xml:id="d533fn9">Telegrams not printed. For texts of
                        convention and protocol of signature, see <ref target="#pg_675">p.
                        675</ref>; for text of final act, see League of Nations document
                        C.455(c).M.193(c).1931.XI (Geneva, August 26, 1931). Texts are also printed
                        in Department of State Conference Series No. 10, pp. 27 ff.</note> Full text
                    of these will only be telegraphed if Department instructs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
